The used cron expression format is 5 columns specifying the execution time (minute, hour, day, month, day of the week), they can contain a numeric list separated by commas, a range of numbers separated by a hyphen, symbols * or /.

Transfer will run regularly at a specified interval. The first run occurs immediately once you save the settings. If you start the transfer manually, next time it will start after the specified interval.
console.form.transfer.RegularSnapshotSet: Wait for transaction completion time, in seconds

Set load delay time to insure that current transactions on source are completed and thus full data is visible for snapshot. This may be useful if source cannot guarantee that cursor values grows monotonically - due to transaction race or well-known problem that serial id sequence does not actually guarantee the order

console.form.transfer.Transfer.type.usag:
Snapshot is transferring of a snapshot of the source to the destination.
Replication is continuously copying changes from the source and applying them to the target.
Snapshot and replication is transferring the current state of the source to the target and keeping it up-to-date.
console.form.transfer.TransferTypeSnapsh: Table data isn't copied completely, but from where the copying ended last time.
Periodic snapshot is transferring a snapshot of the source to the target at given intervals.
